Immigration Department says its officers have arrested 15 Chinese nationals for allegedly engaging in prostitution in Nairobi. The suspects, who were allegedly found in a brothel, in South C estate were taken to Jomo Kenyatta Airport for processing and subsequent deportation. Their arrest comes months after Interior Cabinet Secretary Fred Matiang's declared war on illegal immigrants and foreigners doing jobs that should be done by Kenyans. Two weeks ago, Kenyan police raided the African headquarters of the China Global Television Network in Nairobi and briefly detaining several journalists. The Chinese embassy in Nairobi has complained over police swoops that have seen its nationals with legal documents hauled into police stations for verification.   More follows.   IG Boinnet says 13 staff were arrested and released after their work permits were verified.